    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-16T18:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-16T18:40:00-05:00" n="662"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d662">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/10–1651: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Belgium</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d662fn1">Repeated for information to Geneva for the U.S.
                            <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss> Delegation priority and <gloss
                            target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss> as 97, to Paris for <gloss
                            target="#t_OSR1">OSR</gloss> priority and <gloss target="#t_niact1"
                            >niact</gloss> as 2249, and Ottawa as 105.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-16T18:40:00-05:00"
                            >October 16, 1951—6:40 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>525. Dept informed Belg Govt officials uncertain whether position set out <gloss
                        target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> Gatt 94 Oct 15, rptd Brussels 518, Paris
                    2231, in fact represents coordinated position US Govt. If <gloss
                        target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> thinks high level approach to Belg Govt wld
                    assist in dispelling such doubts, <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> requested
                    make such approach immediately. <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> shld be
                    guided by position set out in reftel.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
